00:12:28,012 --> 00:12:29,412
From my long experience as a detective

220
00:12:29,412 --> 00:12:31,312
and if my premonition is correct,

221
00:12:31,312 --> 00:12:36,012
the culprit is here without a doubt!

222
00:12:38,212 --> 00:12:41,612
And what after this?

223
00:12:41,612 --> 00:12:43,512
President Urai?

224
00:12:43,512 --> 00:12:46,112
Hello! Hey!

225
00:12:46,112 --> 00:12:49,612
He can't answer no matter how much you call him.

226
00:12:49,612 --> 00:12:51,912
Because he's not breathing.

227
00:12:52,751 --> 00:12:55,512
He... he's dead? For real?

228
00:12:55,512 --> 00:12:58,757
Hey. You're joking, aren't you?

229
00:12:58,757 --> 00:13:01,712
Dear? Dear?

230
00:13:01,712 --> 00:13:03,912
Dear!

231
00:13:03,912 --> 00:13:06,765
His mouth smelled like almond.

232
00:13:06,765 --> 00:13:08,767
Cyanide compound poisoning.

233
00:13:10,312 --> 00:13:12,112
